olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 carrot
1 courgette
1 tomato
½ tin sweetcorn
1 packet beef mince
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
2 sachet Louisiana spice blend
1 packet tomato paste
¼ cup water
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
Finely chop the garlic. Grate the carrot and
courgette. Roughly chop the tomato. Drain the
sweetcorn (see ingredients).

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over
a high heat. Cook the beef mince and sweetcorn,
breaking the beef up with a spoon, until browned,
3-4 minutes.

While the beef is browning, spread the mini flour
tortillas over an oven tray lined with baking paper.
Using a fork, poke a few holes in the tortillas to
stop them puffing up as they cook, then lightly
brush (or spray) with a drizzle of olive oil and
season with salt and pepper. Bake the tortillas
until golden and crisp, 6 minutes.
TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between
two trays.
TIP: If you want to serve as tacos instead, no need to
bake the tortillas!

While the tortillas are baking, add the carrot and
courgette to the beef and cook until tender,
3-4 minutes. Add the Louisiana spice blend,
tomato paste and garlic and cook until fragrant,
1 minute. Reduce the heat to medium, then add
the water, stir to combine and simmer until the
chilli has thickened, 2-3 minutes. Season to taste.

In a medium bowl, combine the tomato, a drizzle
of white wine vinegar and a drizzle of olive oil.
Toss to combine.

Bring everything to the table to serve. Build your
tostadas by placing a helping of the beef chilli
on top of a tortilla. Top with shredded Cheddar
cheese, Greek-style yoghurt and tomato salsa.
TIP: Tostadas are piled with ingredients and
eaten like an open sandwich. You can serve the
crisp tostadas on the side of the toppings if you
prefer, or just heat the tortillas and eat with the
filling as tacos!